title.$t: Keith Wann, ASL Comedian, wins Business Mind of the Year

media$title.$t: Keith Wann, ASL Comedian, wins Business Mind of the Year

media$description.$t: in 2010 we saw Keith Wann continue his success with his solo show, producing and starring in the ASL Comedy Tour, doing several ASL Children's Book Stories, being interviewed on NPR and several other radio shows, starting his own ASL Radio show, interpreting on Broadway, marketing involvement with callVRS, establishing Sign Language Access Inc as a 3 service interpreting agency, starting a nonprofit coda365, continuing CruisEUs, getting his mother four cards on mother's day, changing his daughter's diapers without gagging, monthly ASL song club, workshops, and being very modest about it all, it was a complete surprise when he won the Business Mind of the Year...congrats Keith and we hope 2011 is just as busy, that!

content.$t: in 2010 we saw Keith Wann continue his success with his solo show, producing and starring in the ASL Comedy Tour, doing several ASL Children's Book Stories, being interviewed on NPR and several other radio shows, starting his own ASL Radio show, interpreting on Broadway, marketing involvement with callVRS, establishing Sign Language Access Inc as a 3 service interpreting agency, starting a nonprofit coda365, continuing CruisEUs, getting his mother four cards on mother's day, changing his daughter's diapers without gagging, monthly ASL song club, workshops, and being very modest about it all, it was a complete surprise when he won the Business Mind of the Year...congrats Keith and we hope 2011 is just as busy, that!

title.$t: coda365 and Wink Smith Jr

media$title.$t: coda365 and Wink Smith Jr

media$description.$t:
"We are a culture without a land" - Keith Wann

Welcome to our coda365 Non-profit organization. We have been serving the ASL community all of our coda lives.  We are culturally proud of being a coda 365 days of the year and look to embrace our rich history.   A place where codas can feel a sense of belonging through their language and where deaf parents can share their experiences raising their hearing children with their native language.

media$description.$t:

www.coda365.org

media$description.$t:
Someday an ASL Archeological student will discover the coda that was named Keith Wann and revive the lost ASL art of Militant Entertainer, otherwise known as ME. ME was banned from every university and college for being the cause of classifier riots, and body shifting pregnancies with illegal hip thrusts.
All of ME's work was burned...until now...Museum of Illegal Languages presents Keith Wann

title.$t: It's On - Keith Wann "America's Funniest ASL Comedian"

media$title.$t: It's On - Keith Wann "America's Funniest ASL Comedian"

media$description.$t:
Come and rap with Keith Wann as he travels across the ASL Nation performing his one man show in sign language for all to enjoy, relate, and guffaw.  Come laugh your ASL off!
www.KeithWann.com

LYRICS
Keith Wann (Its On)
By mason Page

Now you might think 
Wanns youth was sad
cuz he had a deaf
dear mommy and dad 
but that aint the case
that wasnt his fate
the wanns neva struggled
to communicate

wann no trip man
never had choice
transformed hands 
right into great voice
yep brotha wann make
many peeps laugh
kids wanna get
Wann hot autograph

yall wave ya hands
lift em real high
slap em in rhythm 
its simple as pie

yall wave ya hands
look whos on its the
coda man keith and hes 
numba wann

numba numba WANN
keith is numba wann
everybody clap
cuz the coda mans on!
